      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VOUCHERS (5) brings strong form from Townsville and Cairns the latest, where he was beaten 1L, backed off the map. Has an awkward gate but keeps a top hoop and is on a quick backup. SUPID DATE (7) has been around the mark without winning. Her effort here two back in an Open 3 rates well, but she didn't follow it up at Townsville. Has the inside barrier and could surprise. REPLACE THE ACE (3) switches back to 1560m off a 30-day freshen. Has pieces of form good enough, and winning rider Wiggins is reunited. That's a decent push for his chances, and the gelding has a strong record at the track. GENERAL WOLFFE (4) hasn't won for a long while but showed enough at Rockhampton last time to get some of the minor cash.",
